body:
I'm curious about this style of coding (`Object.keys(argv).forEach(func))` when you're only checking for the presence of a single key).  I would find this more straightforward:

``` js
if (completionOpt in argv) {
  // do whatever
}
```

Are you intentionally guarding against `completionOpt` being in the `Object` prototype?

